'''杜兰线'''（'''Durand Line'''，{{lang-ps|'''د ډیورنډ کرښه'''}}、{{lang-ur|'''ڈیورنڈ لائن'''}}）指[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦]]和[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]长达2430公里的[[边界|边界]]分界线。它最先於1893年訂立作為[[英屬印度|英屬印度]]和阿富汗邊界，由英国外交大臣{{link-en|莫蒂默·杜兰|Mortimer Durand}}与阿富汗国王[[阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗|阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗]]制定，定奪雙方[[勢力範圍|勢力範圍]]界限，並務求改善外交關係和貿易。

早於制定杜兰线以前，阿富汗的外交事務已受到英國箝制，在[[第二次英国-阿富汗战争|第二次英国-阿富汗战争]]期間簽訂的1879年《{{le|甘达马克条约|Treaty of Gandamak}}》已經使阿富汗割讓了[[奎達縣|奎達]]、[[皮辛縣|皮辛]]、赫爾奈、[[錫比縣_(巴基斯坦)|錫比]]、[[古勒姆特區|古勒姆]]和[[開伯爾特區|開伯爾]]地區給英屬印度。因為双方僵持不下，1893年11月12日[[英国|英国]]外交大臣{{link-en|莫蒂默·杜兰|Mortimer Durand}}作为[[英国女王|英国女王]]全权代表与阿富汗国王[[阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗|阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗]]在[[喀布尔|喀布尔]]订约划定。英国人以此作为阿富汗和[[英属印度|英属印度]]的[[边界|分界线]]；该分界线以当时的[[英属印度|英属印度]]政府外交大臣莫蒂默·杜兰主持起草，以其名字命名。杜兰线把一半[[普什图斯坦|普什图族的家園]]劃給英國。1901年，普什图族為主的西北边境省（North-West Frontier Province）設立了，在杜兰线英國的一邊，而當地的一些[[土邦|土邦]]在保持與英國友好的前提下獲允許保留自治權。但是和約簽訂後，[[瓦濟里斯坦|瓦濟里斯坦人]]等部落依然在反抗英國統治。<ref name="at">{{Cite web|url=https://asiatimes.com/2020/04/__trashed-50/|title=Remembering the Faqir of Ipi|website=Asia Times|date=April 16, 2020|access-date=April 17, 2020|archive-date=2020-12-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216204458/https://asiatimes.com/2020/04/__trashed-50/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

1893年11月12日的單頁協議共有七項條款，當中說明不可以干預界線的另一邊。<ref name="LoC-Smith">{{cite web |url=https://www.loc.gov/rr/geogmap/pub/afghanistan.html |title=A Selection of Historical Maps of Afghanistan – The Durand Line |publisher=[[Library_of_Congress|Library of Congress]] |location=United States |first=Cynthia |last=Smith |date=August 2004 |accessdate=11 February 2011 |archive-date=2019-01-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190109025224/http://www.loc.gov/rr/geogmap/pub/afghanistan.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>1894年起英國與阿富汗共同制定停火線，佔了邊界的1300公里。<ref>"The total length of the boundary which had been delimited and demarcated between March 1894 and May 1896, amounted to 800 miles." The long stretch from the [[Kabul_River|Kabul River]] to China, including the [[Wakhan_Corridor|Wakhan Corridor]], was declared demarcated by virtue of its continuous, distinct watershed ridgeline, leaving only the section near the [[Khyber_Pass|Khyber Pass]], which was finally demarcated in 1921: {{cite web
 |url=https://archive.org/stream/historyofafghani031122mbp/historyofafghani031122mbp_djvu.txt
 |title=A History of Afghanistan Vol. II
 |author=Brig.-Gen. Sir [[Percy_Sykes|Percy Sykes]], K.C.I.E., C.B., C.M.G., Gold Medalist of the Royal Geographical Society
 |publisher=MacMillan & Co.
 |year=1940
 |location=London
 |pages=182–188; 200–208
 |accessdate=5 December 2009}}</ref><ref name=Hay>An adjustment to the demarcation was made at [[Arundu|Arundu]] in the early 1930s: {{cite journal
 |last=Hay
 |first=Maj. W. R.
 |title=Demarcation of the Indo-Afghan Boundary in the Vicinity of Arandu
 |journal=Geographical Journal
 |volume=LXXXII |issue=4
 |date=October 1933}}</ref>因應英國與俄羅斯之間的「[[大博弈|大博弈]]」，杜兰线的制定等於讓阿富汗成為兩國在區內的[[緩衝區|緩衝區]]。<ref>{{cite book|title=Battleground: Government and Politics, Volume 1|first=Kathleen|last=Uradnik|page=18|publisher=ABC-CLIO|date=2011|isbn=9780313343131|url=https://books.google.com/?id=uarFTBpg11wC&pg=PA18|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422220524/https://books.google.com/books?id=uarFTBpg11wC&pg=PA18&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>1919年《[[英國-阿富汗條約|英國-阿富汗條約]]》對這條線作出了微調，並在[[印巴分治|印巴分治]]起由巴基斯坦繼承。

由于杜兰线是英国入侵阿富汗时强加给阿富汗当局的，儘管它被國際認可為巴基斯坦西面邊界，阿富汗一直極不願意承認它。<ref name="No change in stance on Durand Line">{{cite news |title=No change in stance on Durand Line: Faizi |url=http://www.pajhwok.com/en/2012/10/24/no-change-stance-durand-line-faizi |date=24 October 2012 |accessdate=11 April 2013 |work=[[Pajhwok_Afghan_News|Pajhwok Afghan News]] |quote=But Afghanistan has never accepted the legitimacy of this border, arguing that it was intended to demarcate spheres of influence rather than international frontiers. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510142126/http://www.pajhwok.com/en/2012/10/24/no-change-stance-durand-line-faizi |archivedate=10 May 2013 }}</ref><ref name="FG">{{cite web |url=http://www.carnegieendowment.org/files/cp72_grare_final.pdf |title=Carnegie Papers – Pakistan-Afghanistan Relations in the Post-9/11 Era |first=Frédéric |last=Grare |date=October 2006 |accessdate=11 February 2011 |archive-date=2017-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808152815/http://carnegieendowment.org/files/cp72_grare_final.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thediplomat.com/2014/02/why-the-durand-line-matters/|title=Why the Durand Line Matters|last=Rahi|first=Arwin|work=The Diplomat|access-date=9 September 2017|language=en-US|archive-date=2019-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729145657/https://thediplomat.com/2014/02/why-the-durand-line-matters/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/joseph-v-micallef/afghanistan-and-pakistan_b_8590918.html|title=Afghanistan and Pakistan: The Poisoned Legacy of the Durand Line|last=Micallef|first=Joseph V.|date=21 November 2015|website=Huffington Post|language=en-US|access-date=9 September 2017|archive-date=2017-10-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171024102621/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/joseph-v-micallef/afghanistan-and-pakistan_b_8590918.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=7tDes7XwARMC&pg=PT358&dq=duran+line+international+recognition#v=onepage&q=duran%20line%20international%20recognition&f=false|title=Afghanistan from the Cold War through the War on Terror|last=Rubin|first=Barnett R.|date=15 March 2013|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=9780199970414|language=en|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422220518/https://books.google.com/books?id=7tDes7XwARMC&pg=PT358&dq=duran+line+international+recognition&hl=en#v=onepage&q=duran%20line%20international%20recognition&f=false|dead-url=no}}</ref>当时英国人划分此线，目的是拆散使其畏惧的[[普什图族|普什图族]]，至今，普什图人一半生活在巴基斯坦控制的边界一侧，另一半在阿富汗边界一侧。第一任阿富汗總統[[穆罕默德·達烏德汗|穆罕默德·達烏德汗]]曾經強烈地反對這邊界並就此發動宣傳戰，但於1976年8月到訪巴基斯坦時他就放軟了態度，承認杜兰线是國際邊界。<ref name="Rasanayagam 2005 64">{{cite book|last=Rasanayagam|first=Angelo|title=Afghanistan: A Modern History|page=[https://archive.org/details/afghanistan00ange/page/64 64]|year=2005|publisher=I.B. Tauris|url=https://archive.org/details/afghanistan00ange|url-access=registration|isbn=9781850438571}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Dorronsoro|first=Gilles|title=Revolution Unending: Afghanistan, 1979 to present|page=84|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FApipiENsgwC&dq|publisher=Hurst & Co. Publisher|year=2005|isbn=9781850656838|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422220500/https://books.google.com/books?id=FApipiENsgwC&dq|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Nunan 2016 125">{{cite book|last=Nunan|first=Timothy|title=Humanitarian Invasion: Global Development in Cold War Afghanistan|page=125|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IL8wCwAAQBAJ&dq|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2016|isbn=9781107112070|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200422220505/https://books.google.com/books?id=IL8wCwAAQBAJ&dq|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last=ur Rahman|first=Hanif|date=December 2012|title=Pak-Afghan relations during Z.A. Bhutto Era: The dynamics of Cold War|url=http://www.nihcr.edu.pk/Latest_English_Journal/Jrnl%2033-2%20(2012)%20PDF/2.%20Pak-Afghan%20Relations,%20hanif%20khan.pdf|journal=Pakistan Journal of History and Culture|volume=XXXIII|pages=34–35|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2020-01-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200110135620/http://www.nihcr.edu.pk/Latest_English_Journal/Jrnl%2033-2%20(2012)%20PDF/2.%20Pak-Afghan%20Relations,%20hanif%20khan.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Durani|first1=Mohib ullah|last2=Khan|first2=Ashraf|date=2009|title=Pakistan-Afghanistan relation: Historic Mirror|url=http://www.qurtuba.edu.pk/thedialogue/The%20Dialogue/4_1/02_ashraf.pdf|journal=The Dialogue|volume=4|number=1|pages=38|access-date=2020-06-28|archive-date=2018-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180826225437/http://www.qurtuba.edu.pk/thedialogue/The%20Dialogue/4_1/02_ashraf.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2017年3月，巴基斯坦總理[[納瓦茲·夏立夫|納瓦茲·謝里夫]]下令重新開放巴基斯坦與阿富汗間的邊界，以與阿富汗一同打擊[[塔利班|塔利班]]在邊界的活動，而阿富汗前總統[[哈米德·卡爾扎伊|哈米德·卡爾扎伊]]明言阿富汗「永不承認」杜兰线是兩國邊界。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Siddiqui|first1=Naveed|title=Afghanistan will never recognise the Durand Line: Hamid Karzai|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1318594|accessdate=9 September 2017|work=[[Dawn_(newspaper)|Dawn]]|date=5 March 2017|archive-date=2019-08-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190804152337/https://www.dawn.com/news/1318594|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 歷史背景 ==
[[File:Afghanistan_region_during_500_BC.jpg|thumb]]和Pactyans]]

被杜蘭線貫穿的地區，自[[古代|古代]]以來已經居住著原住當地的普什圖族。<ref name="LoC">{{cite web |url=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/profiles/Afghanistan.pdf |title=Country Profile: Afghanistan |publisher=[[Library_of_Congress_Country_Studies|Library of Congress Country Studies]] |date=August 2008 |accessdate=11 February 2011 |archive-date=2015-07-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150714051430/http://lcweb2.loc.gov/frd/cs/profiles/Afghanistan.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>在公元前500年左右，[[古希臘|古希臘]]歷史學家[[希羅多德|希羅多德]]提到早於公元前1千年[[阿拉霍西亞|阿拉霍西亞]]裡面和附近已經居住著一個叫「Pactyans」的民族。俾路支部落住在線的南端，一個與[[普什圖族|普什圖族]]分開的地區——[[俾路支斯坦|俾路支斯坦]]。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.piney.com/Heredotus7.html |title=The History of Herodotus, Chapter 7 |publisher=piney.com |translator=George Rawlinson |accessdate=11 February 2011 |archive-date=2012-02-01 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/657c4JeQH?url=http://www.piney.com/Heredotus7.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

[[阿拉伯人|阿拉伯人]]於7世紀征服了當地，把[[伊斯蘭教|伊斯蘭教]]傳給了普什圖族。據指有部分早期的阿拉伯人在[[蘇萊曼山脈|蘇萊曼山脈]]與普什圖族雜居。<ref name="Ferishta">{{cite web|url=http://persian.packhum.org/persian/pf?file=06901021&ct=10|title=''History of the Mohamedan Power in India''|author=[[Firishta|Muhammad Qasim Hindu Shah]] (Firishta)|publisher=[[Packard_Humanities_Institute|Packard Humanities Institute]]|work=Persian Literature in Translation|accessdate=10 January 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090211200506/http://persian.packhum.org/persian/pf?file=06901021&ct=10|archive-date=11 February 2009}}</ref>歷史中普什圖族有「阿富汗族」的稱呼，早至10世紀出現在[[阿拉伯語|阿拉伯語]][[編年史|編年史]]裡。<ref name="Britannica">{{cite web |url=http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9012039/Balochi |title=Baloch |publisher=[[Encyclopædia_Britannica|Encyclopædia Britannica]] Online Version |accessdate=11 February 2011 |archive-date=2008-01-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080108175929/http://www.britannica.com/eb/article-9012039/Balochi |dead-url=no }}</ref>普什圖族的地區（今稱為[[普什圖尼斯坦|普什圖尼斯坦]]）先後被[[加兹尼王朝|加兹尼王朝]]、[[古爾王朝|古爾王朝]]、[[帖木兒王朝|帖木兒王朝]]、[[莫卧儿帝国|-{zh-hans:莫卧儿帝国;zh-hant:蒙兀兒帝國;}-]]、[[漢達基王朝|漢達基王朝]]和[[錫克帝國|錫克帝國]]統治。<ref name="HF">{{cite web |url=http://www.historyfiles.co.uk/KingListsMiddEast/EasternAfghans.htm |title=Kingdoms of South Asia – Afghanistan (Southern Khorasan / Arachosia) |accessdate=16 August 2010 |work=The History Files |date= |archive-date=2019-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190327233450/https://www.historyfiles.co.uk/KingListsMiddEast/EasternAfghans.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1839年，[[第一次英阿戰爭|第一次英阿戰爭]]，[[东印度公司治下的印度|英國]]帶領的印度人軍隊入侵了阿富汗。兩年後的1842年，戰爭以英國戰敗結束。1878年[[第二次英阿戰爭|第二次英阿戰爭]]，英國再度入侵阿富汗。英國成功扶植[[阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗|阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗]]為埃米爾，並於1880年簽署《{{le|甘达马克条约|Treaty of Gandamak}}》。阿富汗把大量前沿地區割給了[[大英帝國|大英帝國]]，加上要落實英國所需的地緣政治需要。

1893年，莫蒂默·杜蘭獲指派到[[喀布爾|喀布爾]]與[[阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗|阿布杜爾·拉赫曼汗]]制定協議，規範兩國的[[勢力範圍|勢力範圍]]，以及改善兩國的外交關係與經貿來往。1893年11月12日，杜蘭線協議達成。<ref name="LoC-Smith"/>雙方之後到了阿富汗[[霍斯特|霍斯特]]附近的{{link-en|帕拉契納|Parachinar}}，今天巴基斯坦[[聯邦直轄部落地區|聯邦直轄部落地區]]境內的一個小鎮，勾畫這一條邊界線。

杜蘭線協議的正本由英文寫成，翻譯本為[[達利語|達利語]]。

協議的後果，就是英方多了一個行政區，今屬於巴基斯坦的西北邊境省。今天它稱為[[开伯尔-普什图省|开伯尔-普什图省]]，包含了联邦直辖部落地区和邊疆區。協議也使阿富汗獲得[[努里斯坦省|努里斯坦省]]和[[瓦罕走廊|瓦罕走廊]]。

